Selected Answer: D
Sorry, 'D', reason;
Internal audit reports are likely to provide the most useful information to assess the magnitude of identified deficiencies in the IT control environment. Internal audit reports are typically conducted by a specialized and independent team that assesses the effectiveness of controls across various areas of the organization. These reports are based on a systematic and comprehensive evaluation of controls, and they typically provide detailed findings, including the scope of deficiencies, their potential impact, and recommendations for remediation. In contrast, while Business Impact Analysis (BIA) results can help identify critical systems and processes, they do not provide as detailed information about the effectiveness of specific IT controls.
